Handles the lowest levels of drawing via the Browser DOM.
Simple application template.
HButton is a control unit that provides the user a simple way to trigger an event and responds to mouse clicks and keystrokes by calling a proper action method on its target class.
HCheckbox is a control unit that allows the user to make multiple selections from a number of options.
HClass class is a simple JavaScript class that eases the pain of JavaScript OO.
Identical to HButton, except has the default action of incrementing its value by one whenever clicked.
ColorValues are HValue extensions used to support the special type of value with special xml output and internal representanion as a fixed size array.
HColorView is a simple box component that display its HColorValue as the color of the box.
HComboBox is a control unit that is a combination of a pop-up-menu, a single-line textfield (textcontrol) and a combobox button.
A HComboBoxButton object displays a labeled pop-up menu.
Define default setting here.
Abstract foundation class for all active visual components that implement events and values.
HDateValues are HValue extensions used to support the special type of value of dates/times with special xml output and internal representanion as a numeric value representing seconds since 1970-1-1 It has the accompanying methods to set date parts, like months and hours.
A HDummyValue is just a placeholder for HValue values.
Handles the mid level event abstraction for components.
HImageButton is the button that has an image.
HImageView is a control unit intended to display images on the screen through the HTML IMG tag.
Serves as a mixin class for classes that need to draw markup but don’t inherit from the HView.
HMenu is a control unit that displays a pull-down or pop-up list of menu items.
A HMenuBar is a menu that can stand at the root of a menu hierarchy.
A HMenuItem object displays one item within a menu and contains the state associated with that item.
Just like HTextControl, but the typed characters are not shown.
Point objects represent points on a two-dimensional coordinate grid.
A HPopupButton object displays a labeled pop-up menu.
HPopupMenu is a control unit that represents a menu typically used in isolation, rather than as part of an extensive menu hierarchy.
HProgressBar is a control unit used to convey the progress of a task, such as a download or file transfer.
A progress indicator is the indeterminate progress bar, which is used in situations where the extent of the task is unknown or the progress of the task can not be determined in a way that could be expressed as a percentage.
HRadiobutton is a control unit that allows the user to choose one of a predefined set of options.
A Rect object represents a rectangle.
This is a special type of HValue.
HRichTextControl is a rich, robust and powerful control unit that allows the user type and edit formatted text.
HTextControl is a control unit that represents an editable rich text.
HSlider is a control unit that enables the user to choose a value in a range of values.
HStepper is a control unit made of two adjacent buttons with up and down arrows to select the previous or next of a set of contiguous values.
HStringView is a view component that represents a non-editable line of text.
HStyleButton is the button that has an image.
Simple application householding system.
HTabBar has no logic functionality at all.
HTabControl is the main component of the HTabBar / HTabLabel / HTabControl / HTabView collection.
HTabLabel displays the ‘tab title button’ above the tab view.
An HTableColumn stores the display characteristics and index identifier for a column and determines the width of its column in the HTableControl.
HTable is a control unit intended to display and organize record-oriented data in the table form.
An HTableHeaderColumn is used by an HTableHeaderView to draw its column headers.
An HTableHeaderView is used by an HTableControl to draw headers over its columns.
HTabBar has no logic functionality at all.
HTextArea is a scrollable multi-line area that displays editable plain text.
HTextControl is a control unit that represents an editable input line of text.
A single instance class.
Simple mid-level AJAX communication system.
HTreeControl is a control unit that displays hierarchical data and allows the user to expand and collapse its nodes.
Node objects are used in a HTreeControl.
Small helper class that acts as the expand/collapse toggler on the node.
Data that needs to be syncronized between components or remote clients should be implemented as HValues.
Simple value syncronization system.
Abstract foundation class for all visual components.
HVSlider (vertical version of the slider control) is a control unit that enables the user to choose a value in a range of values.
Alias for HWindowControl
HWindowBar responds to drag passthrough drag events and is responsible for displaying the HWindowLabel and misc window header stuff, like close, zoom and minimize buttons.
HWindowControl (with alias HWindow) is the main component of the HWindow classes.
HWindowLabel responds to drag passthrough drag events and is responsible for displaying the label of the HWindowBar.
HWindowView has no logic functionality at except basic View management inherited from HView.
